                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/434</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chilean Ambassador brought in Minister Edwards, Chilean Minister to London:</p>
                <p>Discussed the Chilean-Peruvian matter. I impressed on them the necessity of
                    having the matter disposed of. Told them I feared if they did not do it, it
                    would be done at the Peace Conference. It was very evident Edwards wants to
                    force a settlement, but would prefer to have England one of the arbitrators.</p>
            </div>
